HEADWORD: Cathead
<hw>Cat"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A
projecting piece of timber or iron near the bow of vessel, to which the
anchor is hoisted and secured.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

